The paper deals with automatic term extraction from a domain-specific corpus, which is a common problem in natural language processing (NLP) and information retrieval (IR). The use of word embeddings and personalized PageRank algorithm suggests a focus on machine learning (ML) and artificial intelligence (AI) techniques. The paper also evaluates its proposed method on multiple datasets, indicating a focus on experimental evaluation and possibly data mining (DM) or information science (IS). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DL (Deep Learning).
